			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				I don't think we can predict what's going to happen. <br>  <br> On the one hand, some people probably held off logging on to FV to wait until Shadows of Luclin came out, wanting to make a Vah Shir as their character.  (In fact, I know some people held off and said so, although I wouldn't say &quot;hundreds&quot;.) <br>  <br> On the other hand, some people may float on over to other servers to try out a Vah Shir, as you suggest, and simply not return. <br>  <br> Or they may have intended to scrap their characters on FV when SoL came out, so we may also see various people simply vanish. <br>  <br> Then, of course, we also have to factor in the system requirements to run SoL.  My computer is only about a year old, so it can (with a memory expansion), but there are people who are shut out of this expansion who won't migrate at all. <br>  <br> The upshot?  I think it's impossible to say.  We don't know how many people there are in the first, second, or third categories.  We may wind up gaining players; we may wind up losing players; we may end up simply reshuffling the deck some; or, most likely, we'll wind up doing a combination of all three in the first week or so, after which we'll settle back between Vallon Zek and Sullon Zek. <br>  <br> Lasgalen (who likes who he is and doesn't intend to turn into a kitty...  maybe a wolfie, but not a kitty)		

			</td>
